---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Results | Will Harvey | Leadership Growth Consulting"
  description="What actually changes when the structure is right."
>
  <Nav />

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="bg-white pt-28 pb-16 lg:pt-36 lg:pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="text-brand uppercase tracking-widest text-xs font-semibold mb-6">Results</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-zinc-900 leading-tight mb-6 max-w-2xl">
        What actually changes.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 text-xl max-w-xl leading-relaxed">
        I don't have a roster of case studies with percentage lifts and revenue multipliers.
        What I have are business owners who have more space in their week, and businesses that don't
        fall apart when the owner steps back.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CLIENT STORY 1 -->
  <section class="bg-stone-50 py-20 lg:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="text-brand uppercase tracking-widest text-xs font-semibold mb-3">Client story</p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-zinc-900 leading-snug">
            Tax advisory business owner.<br/>6 years. £100k to £3 million.
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:col-span-2 space-y-5 text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            I started working with him in 2020, just before the world shut down. He was a one-man
            band: a desk in a coworking space above a library, revenue around £100k, everything
            running through him. He wanted to grow. But there was no team, no structure, and no
            version of growth that didn't mean working more hours he didn't have.
          </p>
          <p>
            Over six years, we built it together. His team structure, job descriptions, onboarding,
            the systems that let people actually do their jobs without him in every decision. We
            embedded processes that took the operational weight off. We worked out what he should
            be spending his time on versus what he should be handing off. And when it was hard, or
            uncertain, or he just needed someone to help him think through the next move, we worked
            through that too.
          </p>
          <p>
            Six years on, the business is at £3 million. He has a team of people with families of
            their own, and he pays them well. He takes the school holidays off with his kids. He's
            still growing, still on the front foot, still building new service lines. But he does it
            from a position of choice, not obligation.
          </p>
          <p>
            His week now splits between work and sport, a bit like the school timetable he grew up
            on. He spends his time on what he's genuinely best at: the thinking, the vision, the
            new ideas. The business can, largely, run without him in it every day.
          </p>
          <p class="text-zinc-900 font-medium">He built that. I was alongside him every step of the way.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-white py-20 lg:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-zinc-900 mb-4">Want results like these?</h2>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 text-lg mb-8">
        The starting point is a conversation. Book a discovery call and we'll talk about where you are.
      </p>
      <a
        href="https://calendly.com/will-leadershipgrowthconsulting/30min"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="inline-block bg-brand text-white px-8 py-4 font-medium hover:bg-brand-hover transition-colors"
      >
        Book a discovery call
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
